The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, May 8: The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) has relaxed the lending norms for infrastructure projects to encourage banks to earmark more funds at competitive rates. If the date of commercial production extends beyond a period of two years after the completion of the project, as originally envisaged, the account should be treated as sub-standard, the RBI said in a notification.                            
	 Mumbai, May 8: Tata Steel said it had raised Rs 2,000 crore through the private placement of rupee debentures as part of its long-term financing plan, in a filing to the Bombay Stock Exchange.                             
	 Hong Kong, May 8: China Mobile Ltd said it was interested in the South African market but had not bid for MTN, the subject of takeover interest by Indias Bharti Airtel. However, the firms intentions were not disclosed.                            
	 New Delhi, May 8: ICICI Bank CEO K.V. Kamath said there were no indications from the market to signal change in interest rates at the moment, even though the RBI is sucking out over Rs 27,000 crore of the system.                            
	 Calcutta, May 8: The biggest ever exposition of Indian small and medium enterprises (SME) would be held in the US between September 8 to 9 this year.
                                                                                                                               
